\c 1
\p
\v 1 The word of the LORD that came to Micah the Morasthite in the days of
Jotham, Ahaz, \add and\add* Hezekiah, kings of Judah, which he saw concerning
Samaria and Jerusalem. 
\v 2 Hear, all ye people; hearken, O earth, and all that therein is: and let
the Lord GOD be witness against you, the Lord from his holy temple. 
\v 3 For, behold, the LORD cometh forth out of his place, and will come down,
and tread upon the high places of the earth. 
\v 4 And the mountains shall be molten under him, and the valleys shall be
cleft, as wax before the fire, \add and\add* as the waters \add that are
\add* poured down a steep place. 
\v 5 For the transgression of Jacob \add is\add* all this, and for the sins of
the house of Israel. What \add is\add* the transgression of Jacob? \add is it
\add* not Samaria? and what \add are\add* the high places of Judah? 
\add are they\add* not Jerusalem? 
\v 6 Therefore I will make Samaria as an heap of the field, \add and
\add* as plantings of a vineyard: and I will pour down the stones thereof into
the valley, and I will discover the foundations thereof. 
\v 7 And all the graven images thereof shall be beaten to pieces, and all the
hires thereof shall be burned with the fire, and all the idols thereof will I
lay desolate: for she gathered \add it\add* of the hire of an harlot, and they
shall return to the hire of an harlot. 
\v 8 Therefore I will wail and howl, I will go stripped and naked: I will make
a wailing like the dragons, and mourning as the owls. 
\v 9 For her wound \add is\add* incurable; for it is come unto Judah; he is
come unto the gate of my people, \add even\add* to Jerusalem.
\p
\v 10 Declare ye \add it\add* not at Gath, weep ye not at all: in the house of
Aphrah roll thyself in the dust. 
\v 11 Pass ye away, thou inhabitant of Saphir, having thy shame naked: the
