\v 9 The LORD’S voice crieth unto the city, and \add the man of\add* wisdom
shall see thy name: hear ye the rod, and who hath appointed it.
\p
\v 10 Are there yet the treasures of wickedness in the house of the wicked,
and the scant measure \add that is\add* abominable? 
\v 11 Shall I count \add them\add* pure with the wicked balances, and with the
